        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add Gateway system.run MXC runtime E2E proof",
        "body": "Tracking issue: #784\nDepends on: #786\n\n## Summary\n\nPR3 adds focused runtime proof for the real Gateway path:\n\n`Gateway -> node.invoke -> Windows Node -> system.run -> MXC process containment`\n\nThis is intentionally stacked after #786. A focused compare for the PR3 delta is:\n\nhttps://github.com/TheAngryPit/openclaw-windows-node/compare/feature/mxc-26200-sdk-0-7-validation...feature/gateway-system-run-mxc-e2e\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds `RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox` to the E2E setup suite.\n- Adds `RealGateway_SystemRun_BlocksWritesToTrayDataDirectoryInMxcSandbox` to prove a denied write remains contained.\n- Moves the MXC proof into its own gated E2E MXC Setup collection so non-MXC runners skip before heavy setup.\n- The tests provision a fresh WSL Gateway, start an isolated tray instance, set a local exec approval through MCP, invoke `system.run` through `openclaw gateway call node.invoke`, and verify MXC diagnostics in the tray log.\n- The positive test asserts `gateway.nodes.allowCommands` includes `system.run`, `system.run.prepare`, and `system.which` before invoking the proof path.\n- The denied-write test uses a log cursor so it validates diagnostics emitted by the current invocation rather than stale earlier log lines.\n- Documents the focused runtime proof command and required evidence markers in `docs/WINDOWS_NODE_TESTING.md`.\n\n## Validation\n\nFinal-head validation for commit `5ac78183cffe0b4834a004cbc5c3fee326a43d24` on Windows build `26200.8728`:\n\n- Escadinha/base check: PR3 merge-base with current PR2 is `76f9bf39d5c7073fc9775f6e326249f917ef2f71`.\n- `OPENCLAW_RUN_INTEGRATION=1 dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests.csproj --no-restore --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~MxcCommandRunnerIntegrationTests|FullyQualifiedName~MxcCommandRunnerTests|FullyQualifiedName~MxcConfigBuilderTests\" --verbosity minimal`: passed, `82` passed, `0` skipped, `0` failed.\n- `OPENCLAW_RUN_E2E=1 dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.E2ETests/OpenClaw.E2ETests.csproj --no-restore --configuration Debug --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~OpenClaw.E2ETests.Setup.MxcSetupAndConnectTests\" --logger \"trx;LogFileName=pr3-mxc-e2e-final-head-before-push.trx\" --verbosity minimal`: passed, `2` passed, `0` skipped, `0` failed.\n- `openclaw-autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD --engine codex --model gpt-5.5 --thinking high`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings, overall `patch is correct (0.86)`.\n\nRuntime proof markers from the final-head E2E include:\n\n- `gateway.nodes.allowCommands includes system.run/system.run.prepare/system.which`\n- `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_SYSTEM_RUN_MXC_OK`\n- `exitCode=0` for positive execution\n- non-zero exit for denied write\n- denied target file not created\n- `executor=mxc-direct-appc`\n- `contained=True`\n- `shell=cmd`\n- `containment=mxc`\n\n## Installed Companion Runtime Smoke\n\nAs an additional local smoke, a stacked PR3 build was packaged, installed, launched, paired with the real Gateway, and tested through:\n\n`Gateway -> node.invoke -> Windows Node -> system.run -> MXC`\n\nPositive proof:\n\n- Installed Companion launched from `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\OpenClawTray`.\n- Gateway listed the Windows Node as connected.\n- `system.run` returned `ok=true`, `exitCode=0`, and the expected stdout marker.\n- Tray diagnostics showed `executor=mxc-direct-appc`, `contained=True`, `containment=mxc`, `allowOutbound=False`, and `deniedCount=7`.\n\nNegative containment proof:\n\n- A denied write into the app-data/settings area returned `Access is denied.`\n- The command returned `exitCode=1`.\n- The denied target file did not exist after execution.\n- Diagnostics still showed MXC containment for the denied run.\n\nLocal MCP server proof is not claimed here; this validation used the Gateway path.\n\n## Validation boundaries\n\nThis proves the Gateway/Windows-node/MXC runtime path on Windows build `26200.8728` for the observed AppContainer-DACL / `mxc-direct-appc` tier.\n\nIt does not claim:\n\n- Stable-channel Windows proof.\n- `isolation_session` behavior on this build.\n- Local MCP server proof.\n- Full Companion product-feature coverage beyond the Gateway -> Windows Node -> `system.run` -> MXC path.\n\nRefs #784\n",
        "branch": "feature/gateway-system-run-mxc-e2e",
